cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.ST, cs.CE 

The paper describes a Monte Carlo method for likelihood-free models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method is also designed to be embarrassingly parallel, which is a common concern in distributed computing and systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses optimization procedures and validation experiments, which are relevant to statistics and machine learning (cs.ST) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
